There is ambiguity about whether it is a special grand jury or a regular one which has a 30 day term. There was a special grand jury convened in November of last year per Washington Post, but it is unclear whether the DA is using this one. Though these grand juries are convened for a given time, a finding may be presented at any time prior to the end of the specified term. Based on the uncertainty, adjusting for possibility of deliberations running longer than question end date.
